{
  "texts": [
    "Currently, BHK scales are used in the research for constructing the ground truth of the data used for training and evaluation of machine learning-based dysgraphia diagnosis systems.",
    "Machine learning based methodsThis section discusses machine learning based systems for diagnosis of dysgraphia from either the images of handwritten texts or features of writing dynamics.",
    "The general flow of machine learning based dysgraphia diagnosis system is shown in Fig. 6.",
    "As in other machine learning applications, dysgraphia diagnosis systems also follow a similar workflow.",
    "Data collection, preprocessing, feature extraction, feature selection, and training using a machine learning classifier are important steps included in building the machine learningbased dysgraphia diagnosis system."
  ]
}